** sch_path: /foss/designs/cdac/caps_tb.sch
** Final merged CDAC testbench.
** Assembled from: caps.spice (cell body, split MSB/LSB + bridge),
**                 caps_tb.spice (real .subckt pin order + top-level wiring),
**                 testing.spice (complete Dx/Dx_b stimulus + measurements)
**
** NOTE ON PIN ORDER: caps.spice's "**.subckt caps ..." header is a commented-out
** leftover (that file's .subckt/.ends wrappers are all commented, so it netlisted
** as a flat top-level cell). The pin order below is the REAL one, taken from the
** active (uncommented) ".subckt caps" line in caps_tb.spice / testing.spice.

.GLOBAL GND

* ============================================================
* GF180MCU device models -- adjust path if your PDK_ROOT differs
* ============================================================
.include "$PDK_ROOT/gf180mcuD/libs.tech/ngspice/design.ngspice"
.lib "$PDK_ROOT/gf180mcuD/libs.tech/ngspice/sm141064.ngspice" typical
.lib "$PDK_ROOT/gf180mcuD/libs.tech/ngspice/sm141064.ngspice" cap_mim

* ---- nominal (non-Monte Carlo) values for cap_mim's corner/mismatch scaling params ----
* cap_mim_2f0fF's formula (c_cox='1.99e-3*mim_corner_2p0fF', c_c0=...*(1+mc_c_cox_2p0fF)')
* depends on these but they're not defined by .lib cap_mim or design.ngspice;
* for a typical run: corner multiplier = 1, mismatch term = 0.
.param mim_corner_2p0fF=1
.param mc_c_cox_2p0fF=0

* ============================================================
* Top-level instantiation of the CDAC cell (positional, 27 nodes)
* Order: Dx_b<0> Dx_b<1> Dx_b<2> Dx_b<3> Vin Dx_b<4> GND Dx_b<5> Dx_b<6> Dx_b<7>
*        VREF Dx_b<8> phi_s Dx_b<9> Dx<0> VDD Dx<1> Vx Dx<2> Dx<3> Vx_lsb
*        Dx<4> Dx<5> Dx<6> Dx<7> Dx<8> Dx<9>
*
* NOTE ON Vx: "Vx" is only a pin NAME on the .subckt caps definition. At the
* top level it doesn't exist as a node -- positional connection makes it
* alias to net17 (17th pin in the list above). All measurements, wrdata,
* and plot commands below reference net17, not Vx, for that reason.
* ============================================================
x1 net5 net6 net7 net8 net1 net9 GND net10 net11 net12 net3 net13 net4 net14 net15 net2 net16 net17 net18 net19 net20 net21 net22
+ net23 net24 net25 net26 caps

* ---- static rails ----
V1 net2 GND 3.3        $ VDD
V2 net1 GND 0.9        $ Vin (DC -- DAC-only test, no analog input needed for a code-transfer sweep)
V3 net4 GND PULSE(0 3.3 0 1n 1n 30n 300n)   $ phi_s sampling clock -- period re-synced to new 300ns code cadence (was 500n, matching old code hold; duty cycle preserved ~1:10)
V4 net3 GND 1.8        $ VREF -- ### CONFIRM: earlier hand-sizing assumed VREF=1V; this TB uses 1.8V ###

**** full 256-code monotonic sweep stimulus (replaces old spot-check codes A-G) ****
* Each code held 300ns, 256 codes, total sweep = 76800ns
* Dummies Dx<0>(net15)/Dx<5>(net22) tied low permanently, as before.

VDX0  net15 GND 0
VDXB0 net5  GND 3.3

VDX5  net22 GND 0
VDXB5 net10 GND 3.3

